HEADWORD: Crizzel
<hw>Criz"zel</hw> <pr>(kr⟦icr⟧z"z'l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<ets>grizzle</ets> darkish gray, or G. <ets>griselig</ets> gravelly,
granular, speckled.]</ety> <def>A kind of roughness on the surface of
glass, which clouds its transparency.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>crizzeling</asp> and <asp>crizzle</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

